{"article_id":"to8fZ1EWctN6Gp2q","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"It ' s been a bad few weeks for supporters of reproductive freedom .","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"On Tuesday , the Alabama legislature passed one of the most restrictive abortion bills in the country ,","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"banning the procedure with no exception for rape or incest .","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"Last week , Georgia passed a so-called \" heartbeat \" bill","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"that would prohibit an abortion","depth":12},{"id":5,"text":"once a fetal heartbeat can be picked up","depth":12},{"id":6,"text":"- the fourth such bill","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"to be passed in 2019 .","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"These laws will surely be challenged","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"and make their way to the Supreme Court .","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"Once there ,","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"reproductive rights advocates worry","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"that the newly empowered conservative majority ,","depth":14},{"id":13,"text":"entrenched by President Trump in the wake of Justice Anthony Kennedy ' s retirement ,","depth":14},{"id":14,"text":"will use the opportunity","depth":14},{"id":15,"text":"to finally strike down Roe v. Wade .","depth":14},{"id":16,"text":"But not everyone thinks","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"that ' s necessarily what lies ahead .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"The thinking goes that these bills are so extreme","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"that they seem almost designed to be struck down by the high court","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"- and that is of a piece with how the Republican establishment views abortion ,","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"which it basically sees as more effective at ginning up the base","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"when it remains a live issue .","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"The Niskanen Institute ' s Will Wilkinson , a generally astute writer , said of the Georgia bill ,","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"\" it seems pretty clear to me","depth":14},{"id":25,"text":"[ the authors the bill ]","depth":14},{"id":26,"text":"want it to be overturned. \"","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"And why would Republicans want that ?","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"\" They want to keep their base mad","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"and run on it forever ,","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"but never catch the car. \"","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"Following Kennedy ' s retirement in 2018 ,","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"Slate ' s William Saletan explained","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"\" Why Republicans don ' t actually want to repeal Roe. \"","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"Kathleen Parker of the Washington Post , immediately before Trump ' s nomination of Brett Kavanaugh , asserted","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"that no Court majority would want to overrule Roe","depth":15},{"id":36,"text":"and \" be credited with upending settled law","depth":16},{"id":37,"text":"and causing massive societal upheaval . \"","depth":16},{"id":38,"text":"It ' s not an outlandish claim .","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"After all , five Republican nominees were part of the original Roe majority ,","depth":15},{"id":40,"text":"and the decision has now survived more than two decades with a Supreme Court median vote","depth":16},{"id":41,"text":"nominated by anti-abortion presidents .","depth":16},{"id":42,"text":"It seems plausible that Republican elites would rather have Roe on the books","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"to rally the rank and file","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"than pay the political price","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"of overruling it .","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"But this argument fails to withstand serious historical scrutiny .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"The survival of Roe was not the inevitable product of some master Republican plan , but a contingent series of flukes and historical accidents .","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"And just this week , the Court ' s conservative majority showed its willingness","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"to overturn decades-old precedent .","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"Roe still being law in 2019 represents remarkable good luck for supporters of reproductive freedom .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"With Republicans capturing the Senate in 2014","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"and winning the presidency in 2016 ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"and Trump replacing Kennedy in 2018 ,","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"this luck has almost certainly run out .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"The idea","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"that the Republican Party doesn ' t really want to repeal Roe v. Wade","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"- that the landmark abortion case is more useful to it as a mobilizing issue -","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"rests on Supreme Court decisions","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"that were the product less of political scheming and more of happenstance and luck .","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"Roe was in serious jeopardy as early as the late ' 80s ,","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"as the Reagan administration took the position","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"that Roe should be overruled","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"and states passed envelope-pushing statutes","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"to generate test cases .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"In 1989 , the Court issued a ruling in Webster v. Reproductive Health Services ,","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"which considered a Missouri law","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"that defined life as beginning at conception","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"and declared","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"that \" unborn children have protectable interests in life , health , and well-being . \"","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"But Roe survived the first major attempt","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"to dismantle it .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Chief Justice William Rehnquist","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"( who dissented in Roe )","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"tried to assemble a coalition","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"for effectively ending Roe","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"but fell one vote short .","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"The result was an opinion","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"that expressed hostility to Roe","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"without changing the legal status quo .","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"The roadblock was Justice Sandra Day O ' Connor ,","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"who in a concurrence insisted","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"that the Missouri statute did not require the Court to consider","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"whether Roe was correctly decided","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"because the \" fetal personhood \" language did not have concrete legal meaning .","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"Roe survived ,","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"but the threat was clear .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"\" For today , the women of this nation still retain the liberty","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"to control their destinies , \"","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"Justice Harry Blackmun , Roe ' s author , famously wrote in his dissent .","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"\" But the signs are evident and very ominous ,","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"and a chill wind blows . \"","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"By 1991 , the Court ' s two liberal lions , William Brennan and Thurgood Marshall , were gone ,","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"replaced by nominees of President George H.W . Bush .","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"Combined with the four apparent anti-Roe votes in Webster ,","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"this seemed to make overturning Roe a question of \" when , \" not \" if . \"","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"The apparent vehicle was the 1992 case Planned Parenthood v. Casey .","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"The case involved a Pennsylvania statute","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"that imposed several restrictions on abortion","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"that the Court ' s previous applications of Roe had deemed unconstitutional .","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"The American Civil Liberties Union ' s Kathryn Kolbert ,","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"who argued the challenge to the Pennsylvania ' s statute in front of the Court ,","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"essentially assumed","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"that Roe was doomed","depth":15},{"id":104,"text":"and largely dedicated her argument to urging the Court to directly face the question","depth":15},{"id":105,"text":"of whether Roe was still good law ,","depth":15},{"id":106,"text":"rather than continuing to dodge the question","depth":15},{"id":107,"text":"as it had in Webster .","depth":15},{"id":108,"text":"But the expected ruling didn ' t happen .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"After initially voting in conference","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"to overrule Roe ,","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"Justice Anthony Kennedy ended up collaborating with fellow Republican nominees Sandra Day O ' Connor and David Souter","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"to craft a compromise","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"upholding Roe .","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"The essential holding of Roe","depth":16},{"id":115,"text":"- that the 14th Amendment protects the right","depth":17},{"id":116,"text":"to choose to have an abortion prior to fetal viability -","depth":17},{"id":117,"text":"was explicitly reaffirmed .","depth":15},{"id":118,"text":"But Roe ' s \" trimester framework , \"","depth":16},{"id":119,"text":"which forbade virtually any regulation of first-trimester abortions ,","depth":16},{"id":120,"text":"would be replaced with the \" undue burden \" test","depth":16},{"id":121,"text":"O ' Connor had long advocated .","depth":16},{"id":122,"text":"Under the undue burden test ,","depth":16},{"id":123,"text":"which basically held","depth":17},{"id":124,"text":"that a law could not place an undue burden on someone","depth":18},{"id":125,"text":"seeking an abortion ,","depth":18},{"id":126,"text":"the Court struck down Pennsylvania ' s requirement","depth":16},{"id":127,"text":"that a married woman inform her husband","depth":17},{"id":128,"text":"before obtaining an abortion .","depth":17},{"id":129,"text":"But it upheld the statute ' s other regulations ,","depth":15},{"id":130,"text":"including a mandatory 24-hour waiting period and a requirement","depth":16},{"id":131,"text":"that minors obtain the consent of at least one parent .","depth":16},{"id":132,"text":"Casey provided substantially less protection for reproductive freedom than Roe","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"but was still greatly preferable to overruling it altogether .","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"It is this Casey compromise ,","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"crafted by the moderate appointees of Republican presidents ,","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"on which the idea","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"that the GOP doesn ' t really want to repeal Roe","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"largely rests .","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"Was this what Republican elites wanted all along ?","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"There is not , in fact , any reason","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"to believe so .","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"If one looks at the circumstances","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"that brought each of the Casey three to the Court ,","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"it ' s clear that Casey wasn ' t the product of clever scheming by Republicans .","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"O ' Connor was Ronald Reagan ' s first Supreme Court nominee","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"because Reagan had promised to nominate the first female Supreme Court justice .","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"While O ' Connor had displayed some moderation on abortion as a state legislator in Arizona ,","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"she was the most conservative woman","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"who was considered a viable nominee .","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"She wasn ' t chosen","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"because of her relative moderation on abortion .","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"( Indeed ,","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"had Gerald Ford nominated a woman instead of John Paul Stevens in 1975 ,","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"it is highly likely that Reagan would have chosen an anti-Roe conservative as his first nominee . )","depth":13},{"id":155,"text":"Kennedy was confirmed to the Court","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"only because a Democratic Senate rejected Reagan ' s first choice , Robert Bork , an icon in conservative legal circles","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"whom Republican elites certainly wanted to be confirmed .","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"Bork ,","depth":14},{"id":159,"text":"who labeled Roe an \" unconstitutional decision \" in congressional testimony in 1981 ,","depth":14},{"id":160,"text":"unquestionably would have voted to overrule it .","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"Had Reagan nominated another orthodox conservative","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"without Bork ' s extensive history of inflammatory public comments in 1987 ,","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"it is overwhelmingly likely Roe would have been dead in 1990 .","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"( His next pick","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"after Bork dropped out ,","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"Douglas Ginsburg , was also forced to withdraw amid controversy over his personal conduct ,","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"including his admission","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"that he had smoked marijuana several times . )","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"As for Souter","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"- long the bane of conservatives","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"for being a moderate","depth":13},{"id":172,"text":"who got on the Court under a Republican -","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"he was hardly the product of a conscious plan","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"to preserve Roe .","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"As Jan Crawford reported in her book about the Roberts Court ,","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"the Souter choice emerged out of odd intra-administration conflicts ;","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"most notably , some conservatives in the Department of Justice torpedoed the potential nomination of orthodox conservative Ken Starr","depth":15},{"id":178,"text":"because he disagreed with them on an obscure federalism issue .","depth":15},{"id":179,"text":"Bush then went to Souter in large measure because two New Hampshirites in his inner circle","depth":17},{"id":180,"text":"- Chief of Staff John Sununu and Sen. Warren Rudman -","depth":17},{"id":181,"text":"assured him","depth":16},{"id":182,"text":"that Souter was a reliable , solid conservative .","depth":15},{"id":183,"text":"They were wrong ,","depth":13},{"id":184,"text":"but Bush certainly wasn ' t trying to select a liberal .","depth":13},{"id":185,"text":"It ' s worth noting that","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"if Bush had had a secret plan","depth":13},{"id":187,"text":"to preserve Roe ,","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"he likely would not have nominated Clarence Thomas in 1991 , a staunch conservative","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"widely and correctly perceived to be anti-Roe .","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"It ' s also worth noting that in 1991 , there was nothing in the record of Anthony Kennedy","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"- who joined Rehnquist ' s opinion in Webster , not O ' Connor ' s more moderate concurrence -","depth":13},{"id":192,"text":"to suggest","depth":13},{"id":193,"text":"he supported upholding Roe .","depth":13},{"id":194,"text":"That means","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"that","depth":13},{"id":196,"text":"irrespective of Souter ' s position on the question ,","depth":14},{"id":197,"text":"Kennedy voting against Roe ,","depth":16},{"id":198,"text":"as his Webster vote suggested ,","depth":16},{"id":199,"text":"would have made Thomas the fifth and decisive vote .","depth":15},{"id":200,"text":"Now , it ' s fair to say that during this period , Republican presidents were not single-minded about Roe .","depth":9},{"id":201,"text":"But in the years since , abortion has become nothing less than a litmus test .","depth":9},{"id":202,"text":"The rise of the Federalist Society ,","depth":10},{"id":203,"text":"which was founded in 1982","depth":11},{"id":204,"text":"and became steadily more influential over time ,","depth":11},{"id":205,"text":"was in large measure to ensure that another accident like Souter didn ' t happen .","depth":9},{"id":206,"text":"The fact remains , however , that none of the post-1980 Republican justices were selected for the purpose","depth":10},{"id":207,"text":"of preserving Roe .","depth":10},{"id":208,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":209,"text":"had Reagan simply gotten his first choice in 1987 ,","depth":11},{"id":210,"text":"Roe would have been dead .","depth":11},{"id":211,"text":"Since 1992 , Casey has been the controlling precedent on abortion .","depth":9},{"id":212,"text":"Especially after O ' Connor left the Court in 2006 ,","depth":10},{"id":213,"text":"the case has allowed states more and more leeway","depth":12},{"id":214,"text":"to regulate abortion ,","depth":12},{"id":215,"text":"although in 2016 , a Texas law","depth":13},{"id":216,"text":"that would have caused more than half of Texas ' s abortion clinics to close","depth":13},{"id":217,"text":"finally went too far for Kennedy .","depth":12},{"id":218,"text":"With Kennedy no longer on the Court ,","depth":5},{"id":219,"text":"the situation for reproductive rights is about to get worse ;","depth":6},{"id":220,"text":"the only question is how much worse .","depth":6},{"id":221,"text":"It is true that ending Roe would be unpopular ,","depth":7},{"id":222,"text":"which is an argument","depth":9},{"id":223,"text":"pundits like Saletan and Parker have made","depth":9},{"id":224,"text":"about why Republicans won ' t let the law fall in the end .","depth":8},{"id":225,"text":"But it would be odd indeed to use this fact","depth":7},{"id":226,"text":"to conclude","depth":8},{"id":227,"text":"that therefore Republican elites don ' t want it to happen .","depth":8},{"id":228,"text":"Republican efforts","depth":8},{"id":229,"text":"to repeal the Affordable Care Act","depth":9},{"id":230,"text":"and enact Trump ' s tax cuts","depth":9},{"id":231,"text":"were enormously unpopular ,","depth":7},{"id":232,"text":"but they did the latter","depth":7},{"id":233,"text":"and were one vote away from the former anyway .","depth":7},{"id":234,"text":"To see what Republicans really think about abortion ,","depth":7},{"id":235,"text":"just look at the two-track strategy","depth":8},{"id":236,"text":"of doing as much as possible","depth":10},{"id":237,"text":"to limit access to abortion under existing law","depth":10},{"id":238,"text":"while teeing up vehicles","depth":10},{"id":239,"text":"to get Roe overruled .","depth":10},{"id":240,"text":"Ohio is an example of a state","depth":8},{"id":241,"text":"that has pursued both approaches .","depth":8},{"id":242,"text":"In addition to the \" fetal heartbeat \" bill","depth":10},{"id":243,"text":"that directly challenges Roe ,","depth":10},{"id":244,"text":"it has also targeted abortion clinics with onerous legal restrictions ,","depth":9},{"id":245,"text":"with the result","depth":9},{"id":246,"text":"that the number of abortion clinics in the state has been reduced from 45 in 1992 to 10 today .","depth":9},{"id":247,"text":"In addition , the idea","depth":8},{"id":248,"text":"that Roe being overturned will mean","depth":8},{"id":249,"text":"that evangelicals will no longer have the issue","depth":8},{"id":250,"text":"to rally around","depth":8},{"id":251,"text":"is puzzling .","depth":6},{"id":252,"text":"If Roe is overruled ,","depth":6},{"id":253,"text":"the result would be conflicts over abortion laws in most states as well as Congress .","depth":6},{"id":254,"text":"And preserving the movement ' s legislative victories would still require maintaining control of the Supreme Court .","depth":5},{"id":255,"text":"The only hope for Roe , then , lies with Chief Justice Roberts , now the Court ' s median vote on the issue .","depth":5},{"id":256,"text":"Could Roberts ,","depth":10},{"id":257,"text":"who disappointed conservatives","depth":11},{"id":258,"text":"by casting the deciding vote","depth":12},{"id":259,"text":"to uphold most of the Affordable Care Act ,","depth":12},{"id":260,"text":"cross them again","depth":9},{"id":261,"text":"by saving Roe ?","depth":8},{"id":262,"text":"This is highly unlikely .","depth":8},{"id":263,"text":"NFIB v. Sebelius , the vote","depth":11},{"id":264,"text":"that saved Obamacare ,","depth":11},{"id":265,"text":"was a rare exception in Roberts ' s track record ,","depth":10},{"id":266,"text":"and even in that case , he inflicted significant damage on the statute ' s expansion of Medicaid .","depth":9},{"id":267,"text":"From eviscerating the Voting Rights Act to gutting campaign finance law ,","depth":8},{"id":268,"text":"Roberts has generally sided with longstanding movement conservative priorities","depth":9},{"id":269,"text":"even when the results are unpopular .","depth":9},{"id":270,"text":"On abortion , he voted with the minority in the 2016 case to uphold the Texas anti-abortion law ,","depth":8},{"id":271,"text":"which ,","depth":10},{"id":272,"text":"if left in place ,","depth":11},{"id":273,"text":"would in itself effectively render Roe a nullity","depth":11},{"id":274,"text":"by allowing states to stop abortion clinics from operating .","depth":9},{"id":275,"text":"It is true that Roberts has often tried to slowly dismantle precedents","depth":5},{"id":276,"text":"he dislikes","depth":5},{"id":277,"text":"rather than overruling them immediately .","depth":4},{"id":278,"text":"The Court may well take the judicial obfuscation route","depth":5},{"id":279,"text":"in dismantling Roe ,","depth":5},{"id":280,"text":"starting with cases","depth":7},{"id":281,"text":"that give states more leeway","depth":8},{"id":282,"text":"to restrict abortions","depth":8},{"id":283,"text":"instead of explicitly announcing","depth":7},{"id":284,"text":"that it is overruling Roe immediately ,","depth":7},{"id":285,"text":"giving conservative policy victories","depth":6},{"id":286,"text":"without the political costs .","depth":6},{"id":287,"text":"The Court is likely to try to put off consideration of the laws","depth":7},{"id":288,"text":"( like Georgia ' s and Alabama ' s )","depth":7},{"id":289,"text":"that most directly threaten Roe","depth":6},{"id":290,"text":"until after the 2020 elections .","depth":5},{"id":291,"text":"But the willingness","depth":7},{"id":292,"text":"to overturn decades-old precedent","depth":7},{"id":293,"text":"is there .","depth":6},{"id":294,"text":"Just this week , the Court ' s conservative majority ruled , in Franchise Tax Board of California v. Hyatt , to throw stare decisis out the window","depth":11},{"id":295,"text":"and overrule a 1979 decision","depth":12},{"id":296,"text":"on whether a state could be sued in another state ' s courts","depth":12},{"id":297,"text":"-","depth":10},{"id":298,"text":"not because the decision had proven unworkable","depth":11},{"id":299,"text":"or any relevant facts had changed","depth":11},{"id":300,"text":"but because a bare majority of the Court would have ruled differently","depth":11},{"id":301,"text":"had they heard the case in the first instance .","depth":11},{"id":302,"text":"The decision had nothing to do with abortion","depth":9},{"id":303,"text":"- and everything to do with it .","depth":9},{"id":304,"text":"In a dissenting opinion , Justice Stephen Breyer sent up a warning flare :","depth":8},{"id":305,"text":"\" Today ' s decision can only cause one to wonder which cases the court will overrule next . \"","depth":8},{"id":306,"text":"However the Court describes what it ' s doing to Roe ,","depth":7},{"id":307,"text":"in short order , states will have the tools","depth":9},{"id":308,"text":"necessary","depth":9},{"id":309,"text":"to make abortion almost or entirely inaccessible for tens of millions of Americans .","depth":8},{"id":310,"text":"Eventually , the Court will have to face Roe head on ,","depth":4},{"id":311,"text":"and it ' s overwhelmingly likely that it will overrule Roe","depth":5},{"id":312,"text":"if Roberts is the median vote","depth":6},{"id":313,"text":"- and a near certainty","depth":7},{"id":314,"text":"if a Republican president can replace Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg or Stephen Breyer .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":629,"left":589,"right":628,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":589,"left":535,"right":588,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":535,"left":406,"right":534,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":406,"left":369,"right":405,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":369,"left":364,"right":368,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":364,"left":0,"right":363,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":363,"left":329,"right":362,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":329,"left":316,"right":328,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":316,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":328,"left":320,"right":327,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":320,"left":318,"right":319,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":318,"left":3,"right":317,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":317,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":319,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":327,"left":321,"right":326,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":321,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":326,"left":10,"right":325,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":325,"left":11,"right":324,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":324,"left":322,"right":323,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":322,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":323,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":362,"left":330,"right":361,"relation":"elaboration","nuclea